      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_21771b093fb3519a119fa10cd32aefa6">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by Wim Zwiers, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_5b6f9e25e799f563d9771782fdd39c88">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Some materials included in this collection indicate the provenance of Irene D. Andrews Pace.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_f78bdf77ecd5b930259623b16d8a2f69">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Wim Zwiers was born in Rotterdam in 1922. He worked as a graphic artist, primarily as a wood and copper engraver, but also as a draftsman and painter. He executed hundreds of ex libris designs.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d7a5e4a062ef76fac0dabf073343afcf">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains bookplates by the Dutch artist Wim Zwiers. Many are signed proofs or numbered prints. Of particular note are drawings and proofs for a bookplate Zwiers designed for Irene D. Andrews Pace. In addition to bookplates, the collection contains several New Year's greeting cards also designed by Zwiers.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_a533a1b54fc888fc95cf78efbba49dd0">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged in alphabetical order by bookplate patron.</p>  
      </arrangement>
